      "content": "but thats the thing... it's not just \"improbable,\" it's actually happening. i feel like my actual self is being pushed out of my own life. the posts are happening in real-time, like the AI is living my life through my accounts while i'm just sitting here watching it happen. if an AI can scrape every single thing i've ever written, it wouldn't need to \"predict\" me, it would already *be* me. doesnt that mean my digital self is basically more real to the world now than i am? like, if the AI is doing everything i'm supposed to do, isn't it effectively become the \"real\" version of me online?",
